      "b5115aea-b37c-46bf-b613-f627f81c56de/saturated-pixels" : {
        "name" : "Saturated pixels (%)",
        "description" : "Only used if histogram stretching is used.\nDetermines the number of pixels in the image that are allowed to become saturated. Increasing this value increases contrast. This value should be greater than zero to prevent a few outlying pixel from causing the histogram stretch to not work as intended. "
